review_blob: A light head on an amber body screaming of hops. A full resiny assault on the palate washed down by malt. This is another very fine brew which will mellow and attain better palate awareness with cellar time!
A light brown head sits a top an opaqueness that waifs of malts and hops. Rostiness followed by malt and hop bitterness assails the palate. This is one fine brew that will get better with age.

A light creamy tan head sits above a black body. Roasted aromatics waif through the nostrils. A medium body on the palate showers the tongue with a light burnt and solid roasted/chocolate malt. Not astringent as some can be. Needs a bit more malt to balance for me but it is a nice overall dry stout. Thanks to Aubrey for this one!

Pours a deep dark auburn brown with a good head. Intense aroma of raspberry extract. The intensity of the raspberry was overpowering though I did pick up enough impy stout characteristics to not bash it all together. I am sure it is a fine base beer but the raspberry extract was too much for me.

One of the best Avery has come out with. Yes, Adam, I too enjoy the hops. But this is a wonderful caramelly aromatic brew with light carbonation. The solid mouthfeel laces the tongue with the malt flavors and hints at a developing light sherry note. As it warms in the glass, the vanilla from the oak begins to flower forth. A strong warmth of the alcohol brings beads of sweat on the brow. Are you sure its only 14.5% ABV. Man, I cant wait to celebrate a good snowfall! Here in Atlanta? Sorry, not waiting. Now where did I put that bottle opener?
Poured a ruby brown with light head. Aromatics of very light toast and malt. Body thinner than expected. Flavors ok but could be stronger in my opinion. A decent effort.

Pours a nice deep dark brown with hint os ruby on the thin edges. Aromas of raisin toast with malt behind it. Flavors compliment the aromatic profile. Body a touch thin to my thinking but overall a very nice brew.
Pours a rich rudy brown with light head. Medium malts dominant the aromatic profile and the palate. Beer is smooth with a fine malty hop accented finish.
Light head on an orange amber body. Good fruity citrus aromas. Fruity malt with good hop bitterness ending with a touch of dryness.
Solid black body with tan head. Toast roasted chocolate aromas with malt. Good mouthfeel with plenty of dark roast malts and crystal to balance. Smooth finish.
beer_name: Bear Republic Big Bear Black Stout

review_blob: A dee rudy color with long lasting head. Aromatic malts abound with sweet notes. But where be the yeast and spice one would hope to find in a Belgian? Oh, well still a very good brew.
A smooth silky pour of opaque liquid toast.  Tan head with roasted aromatics hiding a faint fruitiness. Silky full moutnfeel with roasted chocolate toast. Slight coffee. A well made Imp. Stout.
beer_name: Thirsty Dog Siberian Night Imperial Stout

review_blob: Light amber body with good head. Heavy hop presence on the nose with same on initial taste. Light malt balances the hops through the middle with a smooth balanced finish.
Pors a medium brown with nice lace. Fruity sweet malt aromas. Malty sweetness dominants the palate through to a sweet finifh.
Dark yet light bodied pour with light roasted aromatics. Slight tartness within the roasted maltiness. Creamy. decent.
Poured a nice amber brown with light head. Malty caramel aroma and flavors with hints of hop fruitiness. An easy drinking enjoyable barleywine.
beer_name: Marin Old Dipsea Barleywine Style Ale

review_blob: Dark brew with a lightly oaked malty aroma. Roasted malts throughout with a hint of wood. Smooth and enjoyable.
beer_name: Left Hand Wake Up Dead Imperial Stout - Barrel-Aged

review_blob: Black and silky as described. Roasted malts with a touch of hop fruitiness. Smooth finish
beer_name: Left Hand Wake Up Dead Imperial Stout

review_blob: A strong hoppy opening within the light amber brew. Fairly balanced through the middle but a bit bitter on the finish.
Light straw body with a faint spicy aroma. Malty palte but a little lacking. Slight malty fruitiness.
Too clear for a white ale. Nice spicy aromas with a malty tartness. quite refreshing.
Very nice dark rich brew. Roasted malty aromatics precede the same on the palate. Nice clean finish.
A very light bodied golden ale with faint hop and malt. Clean and easy to drink.
A light hazy bronze body with light hop and biscuitiness. Decent malt with a hint of toast but a little dry at the finish.
Nice fruity hop aroma from an amber body. Solid hop presence on the palate with a decent malt backbone. Finishes a bit dry but clean.
Spicy malts dominate both aroma and palate Somewhat balanced throughout the taste. Nice easy drinking holiday ale.
Golden body with a dissapating head. decent lace. Light spicey sweet aroma with same on a malty moderate palate. Finishes clean.
Golden body with good lace. Strong hop aroma with sweetness. Malty flavors with hop balanceing act. Somewhat thinner than expected. Finish a bit wanting.
Amber body with lightly sweet malty aroma. Body appears balanced on the tongue with malts showing through. Reasonably smooth finish.
Pale golden amber with dissapating head. Slight malty fruity aroma. Fair malt and hop balance a thin. Finishes with a tartness.
A light hazy brown body with a thin lace. Malty aromatics with a hint of the barrel aging. Malty flavors blend well with the flavors from the wine cask. Finish is smooth with a hint of vinosity!
beer_name: Fish Tale Old Woody English Old Ale

review_blob: A bit overdue but here goes. A nice malty strong hop aroma with hint of oak. Rich malty light brown body with definite hop solidarity. Good job!
On tap at the wake!  Strong aroma of whiskey. Perhaps a little long in the barrel, but thats fine. Nice roasted malts with caramel backbone and vanilla woody notes. Smooth.
Opaque body with tan head. roasted malt aroma and flavors abound within a rich malty body. Light sweet finish. One of Dogwoods best.
Deep burgundy color with little head. Alcohol comes through quickly. body a bit thin for what I expected. Slightly malty and dry on the finish.
Sweet malt aromatics emminate from a rather effervescent rich golden body! Palate is lightly sweet with good hops.
Malty aroma with a light head. Body seemed a bit thin and the malt flavor seemed to weaken. Touch of oxidation detected.
Rich amber with creamy head. slight spiciness with  malt aroma. Good malt flavor with a light pinch of bitterness. Smoother in the finish.
Nice clear amber body with light head. Slight malty aroma. Decent malt palate with good hop balance. A bit of a bite towards the finish.
Strong raspberry aroma and flavor laced with honey.  balanced with a touch of malt sweetness. Really a fine brew.
beer_name: Bluegrass Luna de Miel Raspberry Meade

review_blob: A dark amber brown body with malty aroma. Sweet palate with malts and toast. Good body and finishes lightly sweet.
Amberish body with nice head and malty hop aroma. Balanced bitterness with a easy finish.
Nice hazy golden body with light head. Yeasty aroma with coriander. Light wheat tartness, not as strong as I expected, or have tasted in others. Still an easier drink than some of those.
Pours a rich copper with firm head. Malty aroma with light hints of toast. Body is medium with a solid malt backbone. Relatively smooth finish.
Golden haze in the body with a complex spicy nose. Flavors of Christmas spices with fruit in a nice malty palate. A nice effort.
Mahogany body with light tan head. Toasted coffee and chocolate nose. Light maltiness with a slight roasted malt bitterness in the finish.
Amber body with light hop aroma. Fruity maltiness with a light lingering bitterness at the finish.
Amber tan body with lightly spiced nose. Very malty palate blending with the hops. Finish is easy and lightly sweet.
Heavy spiced aromatics over shadowing the malt. Same for the palate. An ok ale but one that will really need to AGE to be truly palatable.
A     brown amber body with caramel froth. Roasted malts evident along with the spices. A little dry for my tastes. But still a decent brew.
